          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(center)">
                                        <placeName>Montgomery</placeName>
                                        <date>23 August 1852</date>
                              </p>
                              <p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Sir!</p>
                              <p>I enclosed send you three Dollars for a copy<lb/> of the Occident,
                                        which you have send to the <persName>Rev E.<lb/>
                                                  Marmson</persName> of this city (formerly.)</p>
                              <p>I believe you have been already informed, the<lb/> circumstances,
                                                  <sic>conected</sic>
                                        <sic>whit</sic> the <persName>Rev. E.
                                        Marmson</persName><lb/> but if not? I will tell you</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">The Kahl of this city—(I am not a member)<lb/> had
                                        engaged <persName>Mr Marmson</persName> for a year
                                        payable<lb/> quarterly at the rate of $500 a year.
                                                  <sic>Thee</sic>
                                        <sic>wuld</sic><lb/> not agree, and <persName>Mr
                                                  Marmson</persName> send his resignation<lb/> and
                                        left them and went to the Ministers of the<lb/> Christian
                                        Faith, he has then for the last 6 or 8<lb/> weeks boarded
                                        and lodged <sic>whit</sic> them and the<lb/> rumor here in
                                        this city, was, that he has been<lb/> converted to the
                                        Christian faith,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I meet then <persName>Mr Marmson</persName> and
                                        ask him of<lb/> the truth, he then <sic>denided</sic> and
                                        said all is<lb/> a Lie, and false. I told him that he
                                        should<lb/> to <sic>satisfied</sic> the Brothers of our
                                        faith, and the<lb/>
                                        <sic>comunity</sic> in <sic>generally</sic>, publish the
                                        truth in the city<lb/> papers, under his own signature,
                                        which he<lb/> promise me to do it, but in vain he left<lb/>
                                        here I do not <sic>wer</sic> he went to and <sic>dit</sic>
                                        not <sic>don</sic><lb/> it. I send you this information to
                                        satisfy</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>you and our Brothers in the <placeName>United
                                                  <sic>Stated</sic></placeName> to have<lb/> a look
                                        out and to be on their guard.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">And I no say If <persName>Mr Marmson</persName>
                                        <sic>dos</sic> not<lb/> publish the truth in your
                                                  <sic>Pamplet</sic> our Asmonean<lb/> under his own
                                        signature?</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I will then publish his name over<lb/> the
                                        world</p>
                              <p rend="indent(6)">More anon</p>
                              <p rend="indent(7)">Yours Truly</p>
                              <p rend="indent(7)">
                                        <persName role="author">S. Cellner</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>P. S.  The three Dollars for the Occident<lb/>   I have received of
                                        the President<lb/>   from Kahl for him——</p>
                    </body>
